<!--STORY 5-->

<font size="+1"><b>In what business do we trust?</b></a></font><br>

In response to my recent column, "<a href="http://clickthru.online.com/Click?q=45-fNkJIKBij6jkp0x-EDvznhjonlZR" ><B>Desperately seeking chief ethics officer</B></a>," <B>David Boulton</B> writes: "We are missing the point when we focus on the executives of corporations and miss the underlying ethic of business in general." Boulton asks how we can possibly trust institutions that reduce human beings "to assets whose behaviors are fair game to manipulate?"

<br><img src="http://www.zdnet.com/techupdate/i/arrow_blue.gif" width="8" height="10" border="0">
<a href="http://clickthru.online.com/Click?q=5a-ahD1IP0zdKnCnKw24YOLpk6Td6dR" >
